feedback: I enjoyed this study very much.  The way it was presented was unique.  The links and buttons that provided more information was a good way to keep the participant focused and engaged.  The only problem is that these types of studies that contain multiple writing tasks can vary wildly in the time it takes to complete.  That all depends on the person taking it, and how long it takes them to express their thoughts.  I see you tried to limit that a bit by asking for only 1-2 sentences, but even then I tend to take much longer than anticipated when I have a lot of writing tasks to do. That's probably exacerbated by the abundance of click-only studies we get, so when you get one that asks us to elaborate on thoughts, we go a little overboard. Not complaining here, just an observation about my own tendencies.  Curious if it's the same for many others.
